		<td>XML</td>
		<td>TIGER XML is used for encoding sentences (or other
			linguistically meaningful segments) which have been
			annotated with directed acyclic graphs. This means that a
			wide range of linguistic descriptions like syntax trees,
			functional structures, dependency-style structures,
			predicate-argument structures can be accommodated.
			A node in a TIGERSearch graph structure may be labelled with
			a feature record. A feature record is a restricted form of a
			feature-value structure or attribute-value structures as
			known from unification-based grammar formalisms. TIGER XML 
			is described in the following <a
			href="http://www.ims.uni-stuttgart.de/projekte/corplex/paper/lezius/lrec2000.pdf">paper</a>.
			</td>
